Show HN: LibmCS – (Pre-)Qualified Mathematical Library for Critical Systems
text:
This is the mathematical library for critical systems (LibmCS).

It has been developed in compliance with the European Cooperation for Space Standardization (ECSS) standards E-ST-40 and Q-ST-80 to criticality Category B and it is also compliant to the standards:

IEEE-754, C18, POSIX, and MISRA C The library has been developed by GTD GmbH under the ESA Contract No. 4000130278/20/NL/AS.

Documentation: https://gtd-gmbh.gitlab.io/libmcs/ (User manual, Design documentation)

Show HN: A FUSE module to work with FASTA files
text:
Hello HN, we recently published FUSTA, a piece of software that tries to alleviate the pain of reading & writing huge FASTA files, which is something that we meet quite frequently.

FUSTA leverages FUSE to expose a FASTA file as a hierarchy of sequence files, either raw or in the FASTA format, and let you either read them as individual files, or rename/delete/edit/add some of them.

Thought it may be of interest to the biologists/bioinformaticians here; we use it on macOS, Linux & FreeBSD, feedback & suggestions welcome!

Revolutionizing the Future of Cybersecurity with Quantum-Proof Encryption
text:
In today's digital age, protecting sensitive data has become a top priority for organizations and individuals alike. However, as quantum computing technology advances, traditional encryption methods such as RSA and AES are becoming increasingly vulnerable to hacking. This is where quantum-proof encryption, also known as post-quantum encryption, comes in.

Quantum-proof encryption utilizes advanced algorithms that are resistant to attacks from quantum computers, providing an unprecedented level of security for your data. This includes methods like Lattice-based encryption and Code-based encryption that use complex mathematical properties to encrypt data.

Don't let your organization fall victim to a cyber attack. By implementing quantum-proof encryption, you can have peace of mind knowing that your data is secure and protected against even the most advanced forms of hacking. With its ability to safeguard sensitive information and pave the way for a safer digital future, quantum-proof encryption is truly the future of data security.

By making your message more professional and engaging, it will encourage readers to take action and consider using this technology for their organization security. Also it highlights the importance of the technology and how it's a step ahead from the current encryption methods.
